Cyber security guide for individuals

Guide to Good Cybersecurity for Individuals

Strong Passwords: Use strong, unique passwords for each account. Avoid easily guessable passwords.

Two-Factor Authentication (2FA): Enable 2FA for added security.

Keep Software Updated: Regularly update your OS, antivirus, and other software.

Be Cautious with Emails: Avoid opening suspicious emails or clicking on unknown links.

Secure Your Wi-Fi: Change router passwords, use encryption, and avoid public Wi-Fi for sensitive activities.

Use Secure Websites: Look for "https://" and a padlock icon in the address bar.

Backup Your Data: Regularly back up important files to external drives or cloud storage.

Social Media Privacy Settings: Adjust privacy settings to control who can see your information.

Be Careful with Personal Information: Avoid sharing sensitive information online unless necessary.

Education: Stay informed about cybersecurity threats and techniques.

Use a Firewall: Enable a firewall on your device.

Stay Vigilant: Be cautious of unsolicited messages or offers.





